  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 800 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Zest @lemon{1} until you have 1 tsp zest, then cut into quarters. Place @sour cream{6%tablespoon} in a #shallow dish{}. In another shallow dish, mix @panko breadcrumbs{1%cup}, @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, lemon zest, @paprika{1%teaspoon}, and half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}. Season with plenty of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.

Line a #baking sheet{} with #aluminum foil{} and sprinkle with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Pat @chicken legs{32%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Coat chicken all over with sour cream, then dip into panko mixture, coating all over and pressing to adhere. Transfer to foil-lined sheet.

Bake chicken on middle rack until cooked through, ~{35-40%minutes}. 
> Chicken is done when thickest part of thigh reads 165 degrees on a thermometer.

Meanwhile, trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Once water boils, add @macaroni pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until a bit shy of al dente, ~{7-9%minutes}.

After 7-9 minutes, add @peas{8%ounce} to pot with macaroni. Cook until peas are tender and macaroni is al dente, about ~{2%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup cooking water, then drain. Return empty #pot{} to stove, add @garlic herb butter{2%tablespoon}, and melt over medium heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, about ~{1%minute}.

To pot with scallion whites, add ¼ cup cooking water, remaining Parmesan, and @Italian cheese blend{1%cup}, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}. Whisk until smooth and creamy. Gently stir macaroni and peas into pot.
> TIP: Everything should be coated in a loose sauce. If thick, add more cooking water 1 TBSP at a time until creamy.

Season with salt and pepper.

Divide pasta and chicken between plates. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve with lemon quarters on the side for squeezing over.